title: Introduction to Chemistry
description: Covers the scientific method, branches of chemistry, significant figures, dimensional analysis, and laboratory safety protocols.

title: Atomic Theory and Structure
description: Includes early atomic models (Dalton, Rutherford), subatomic particles, isotopes, atomic mass calculations, and the Bohr model.

title: Electronic Structure of Atoms
description: Focuses on quantum numbers, electron configurations, orbital diagrams, the Aufbau principle, Pauli exclusion, and Hund's rule.

title: Periodic Table and Properties
description: Covers periodic trends including atomic radii, ionization energy, electron affinity, electronegativity, and block classifications.

title: Chemical Bonding I (Ionic & Covalent)
description: Covers Lewis structures, lattice energy, formal charges, covalent bonding, and bond polarity.

title: Chemical Bonding II (Geometry)
description: Focuses on VSEPR theory, molecular shapes, hybridization (sp, sp², sp³), molecular orbitals, and intermolecular forces.

title: Stoichiometry and Reactions
description: Includes the mole concept, balancing equations, limiting reagents, percent yield, and reaction types.

title: States of Matter and Gas Laws
description: Covers Ideal Gas Law, partial pressures (Dalton's Law), real gases, and properties of solids and liquids.
paperType: States of Matter and Gas Laws

title: Thermochemistry
description: Focuses on enthalpy changes, calorimetry, Hess's Law, standard enthalpies of formation, and heat transfer.

title: Chemical Equilibrium
description: Covers Le Châtelier’s principle, equilibrium constants (Kc, Kp), reaction quotients, and law of mass action.

title: Acids, Bases, and Salts
description: Includes pH/pOH calculations, Arrhenius and Brønsted–Lowry theories, salt hydrolysis, and acid strength.

title: Buffer Solutions and Titrations
description: Focuses on buffer mechanisms, the Henderson–Hasselbalch equation, titration curves, and indicators.

title: Chemical Kinetics
description: Covers reaction rates, rate laws, order of reaction, activation energy, and catalysis.

title: Redox and Electrochemistry
description: Includes balancing redox reactions, oxidation numbers, electrochemical cells, and standard electrode potentials.

title: Introduction to Laboratory Chemistry
description: Covers laboratory apparatus, experimental errors, solution preparation, qualitative analysis, and data reporting.
